parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure due to Rust
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake lines due to rust can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and uncontrolled acceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. Oil sludge can also cause engine damage and failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failed engine mounts can cause the engine to shift or move excessively, leading to vibrations, noise, and potential engine damage.
